    "title": "How to Choose Valves & Hose Fittings: Complete Buying Guide for Industrial Applications",
    "slug": "how-to-choose-valves-hose-fittings-buying-guide",
    "content": "{\"root\":{\"type\":\"root\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Valves and hose fittings are essential components in industrial plumbing and pump systems, used to control, direct, and regulate the flow of fluids. These products ensure efficient and safe operation of various industrial processes.\",\"format\":0,\"detail\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\"}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"textFormat\":0,\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"tag\":\"h2\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Why Valves & Hose Fittings Matter for Industrial Operations\",\"format\":0,\"detail\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\"}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Valves and hose fittings play a critical role in maintaining the integrity and efficiency of fluid handling systems. Properly selected and installed, they provide reliable control over the flow of liquids and gases, ensuring that operations run smoothly and safely. They help prevent leaks, reduce downtime, and minimize the risk of accidents, making them indispensable in any industrial setting.\",\"format\":0,\"detail\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\"}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"textFormat\":0,\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"tag\":\"h2\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Key Factors to Consider When Choosing Valves & Hose Fittings\",\"format\":0,\"detail\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\"}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"list\",\"listType\":\"bullet\",\"start\":1,\"tag\":\"ul\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"listitem\",\"value\":1,\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Material: The material of the valve or fitting should be compatible with the fluid being handled. Common materials include brass, stainless steel, and plastic, each with its own advantages and limitations. For example, brass is corrosion-resistant and durable, making it suitable for water and air applications, while stainless steel is ideal for harsh environments and high-pressure systems.\",\"format\":0,\"detail\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\"}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"version\":1}}",
    "category": "buying-guide",
    "tags": "[\"valves\",\"hose fittings\",\"industrial plumbing\",\"MRO supplies\"]",
    "author": "Machrio Technical Team",
    "status": "published",
    "published_at": "2026-03-01T14:11:48.250Z",
    "created_at": "2026-03-01T14:11:48.250Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-03-01T14:11:48.250Z"
