  {
    "title": "How to Choose Seals & Gaskets: Complete Buying Guide for Industrial Applications",
    "slug": "how-to-choose-seals-gaskets-buying-guide",
    "content": "{\"root\":{\"type\":\"root\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Seals and gaskets are critical components in industrial machinery and equipment, providing a barrier between two surfaces to prevent leaks, contain pressure, and maintain the integrity of mechanical systems. They come in various materials and designs, each suited for specific applications and environments.\",\"format\":0,\"detail\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\"}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"textFormat\":0,\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"tag\":\"h2\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Why Seals & Gaskets Matter for Industrial Operations\",\"format\":0,\"detail\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\"}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Seals and gaskets play a vital role in ensuring the reliability and efficiency of industrial operations. They provide a seal that prevents fluid or gas leakage, maintains pressure, and protects against contamination. Properly selected and installed seals and gaskets can significantly reduce downtime, lower maintenance costs, and enhance safety. For example, a high-quality gasket can ensure that a pump operates efficiently without leaks, thereby extending its lifespan and reducing the risk of environmental contamination.\",\"format\":0,\"detail\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\"}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"textFormat\":0,\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"tag\":\"h2\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Key Factors to Consider When Choosing Seals & Gaskets\",\"format\":0,\"detail\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\"}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"list\",\"listType\":\"bullet\",\"start\":1,\"tag\":\"ul\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"listitem\",\"value\":1,\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Material: The material of the seal or gasket must be compatible with the media it will contact (e.g., oil, water, chemicals). Common materials include rubber, silicone, PTFE, and metal.\",\"format\":0,\"detail\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\"}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"version\":1}}",
    "category": "buying-guide",
    "tags": "[\"seals-gaskets\",\"power-transmission\"]",
    "author": "Machrio Technical Team",
    "status": "published",
    "published_at": "2026-03-01T14:31:52.008Z",
    "created_at": "2026-03-01T14:31:52.008Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-03-01T14:31:52.008Z"
